I assume you are hitting these issues when building with TensorRT 8.2 ?

We've been testing trt 8.2 in this [dev branch](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/tree/jywu_docker_trt82)
building onnxruntime with TRT EP using a base image created from https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/jywu_docker_trt82/tools/ci_build/github/linux/docker/Dockerfile.manylinux2014_cuda11_4_tensorrt8_2 and it is all working fine. 
is there some difference in the version of protobuf you're using vs what onnx-tensorrt expects?

What version does it expect (they only say "Protobuf >= 3.0.x")?
We do have `-Donnxruntime_PREFER_SYSTEM_LIB=ON` so if that's passed to onnx-tensorrt via ort, then it's using the system installed one, which is the latest protobuf release.

https://github.com/onnx/onnx-tensorrt/issues/735 may be related, but it basically says onnx-tensorrt doesn't work on protobuf>=3.6, which is 4 years old.

And aside from protobuf, don't forget about the cuda part.

the cuda_runtime_api.h error is due to mismatch between TensorRT version and onnx-tensorrt version.  (8.2 vs 8.0)
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/9981 updates ORT master to support TensorRT 8.2 (by updating onnx-tensorrt submodule to latest which supports TensorRT 8.2)
we should be merging that into master branch soon.

> [onnx/onnx-tensorrt#735](https://github.com/onnx/onnx-tensorrt/issues/735) may be related, but it basically says onnx-tensorrt doesn't work on protobuf>=3.6, which is 4 years old.
> 
> And aside from protobuf, don't forget about the cuda part.

according to https://github.com/onnx/onnx/issues/2678  , it's >= 3.11 , not 3.6
seems like onnx had that issue and it was recently fixed by https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/3112
we can apply the same fix in onnx-tensorrt (will raise with Nvidia maintainers)
